  "prompt": "What is origin of \"Nehru\" surname?",
  "response": "The surname \"Nehru\" is of Indian origin and is associated with the prominent Nehru family, which played a significant role in India's struggle for independence and its subsequent political landscape. The name \"Nehru\" is derived from the Persian word \"nahar,\" which means \"canal.\" It is believed that an ancestor of the Nehru family, Raj Kaul, was a Kashmiri Pandit who migrated to Delhi in the 18th century and was granted a canal as a jagir (land grant) by a Mughal emperor. As a result, the family came to be known as \"Nehrus,\" signifying their association with the canal.\n\nThe most famous member of the Nehru family is Jawaharlal Nehru, who became the first Prime Minister of independent India in 1947 and served until 1964. His daughter, Indira Gandhi, also served as Prime Minister, as did her son, Rajiv Gandhi. The Nehru family's legacy continues to be an important part of Indian political history.",
